from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
 
y = merged_df['feature591']  # Replace 'target_column_name' with the name of your target column
 
# Dropping the target variable from the dataframe to get only the features
X = merged_df.drop('feature591', axis=1)
 
# Split pass cases into training and testing sets while preserving the distribution
X_pass_train, X_pass_test, y_pass_train, y_pass_test = train_test_split(
    X[y == -1], y[y == -1], test_size=0.25, random_state=42, stratify=y[y == -1])
 
# Split fail cases into training and testing sets while preserving the distribution
X_fail_train, X_fail_test, y_fail_train, y_fail_test = train_test_split(
    X[y == 1], y[y == 1], test_size=0.25, random_state=42, stratify=y[y == 1])
 
# Concatenate the pass and fail cases in training and testing sets
X_train = pd.concat([X_pass_train, X_fail_train])
y_train = pd.concat([y_pass_train, y_fail_train])
X_test = pd.concat([X_pass_test, X_fail_test])
y_test = pd.concat([y_pass_test, y_fail_test])

print("Testing set - Features:", X_test.shape, "Labels:", y_test.shape)

Replace Outliers-3s¶

In [165]:
# Define function to replace outliers with 3s boundaries
def replace_outliers_with_3s_boundaries(data, threshold=3):
    # Calculate z-scores for each feature
    z_scores = (data - data.mean()) / data.std()
    
    # Identify outliers
    outliers = np.abs(z_scores) > threshold
    
    # Replace outliers with 3s boundaries
    data_cleaned = data.copy()
    data_cleaned[outliers] = np.sign(data[outliers]) * threshold * data.std() + data.mean()
    
    return data_cleaned

# Replace outliers in training and test sets with 3s boundaries

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.impute import KNNImputer
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# Assuming X_train_cleaned, X_test_cleaned are your cleaned DataFrames
# Initialize the scaler and KNN imputer with desired parameters
scaler = StandardScaler()
knn_imputer = KNNImputer(n_neighbors=5)

# Fit and transform scaler on X_train_cleaned
X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_cleaned)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_cleaned)

# Fit and transform the imputer on scaled X_train_cleaned
X_train_imputed_scaled = knn_imputer.fit_transform(X_train_scaled)

# Transform X_test using the fitted imputer
X_test_imputed_scaled = knn_imputer.transform(X_test_scaled)

# Inverse transform to get back original scale
X_train_imputed = scaler.inverse_transform(X_train_imputed_scaled)
X_test_imputed = scaler.inverse_transform(X_test_imputed_scaled)

# Convert the numpy arrays back to DataFrames
X_train_imputed = pd.DataFrame(X_train_imputed, columns=X_train_cleaned.columns)
X_test_imputed = pd.DataFrame(X_test_imputed, columns=X_test_cleaned.columns)

# Print the shapes of the imputed DataFrames to verify
print("Shape of X_train_imputed:", X_train_imputed.shape)
print("Shape of X_test_imputed:", X_test_imputed.shape)

from boruta import BorutaPy
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Example: Initialize Boruta and fit it
forest = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
boruta_selector = BorutaPy(forest, n_estimators='auto', random_state=42)
boruta_selector.fit(X_train_imputed.values, y_train.values.ravel())

# Get feature names and Boruta rankings
feature_names = data.columns
boruta_rankings = boruta_selector.ranking_

# Create a list of tuples (feature, ranking) and sort by ranking
features_with_ranking = list(zip(feature_names, boruta_rankings))
features_with_ranking_sorted = sorted(features_with_ranking, key=lambda x: x[1])

# Extract sorted feature names and rankings
sorted_features = [feat for feat, rank in features_with_ranking_sorted]
sorted_rankings = [rank for feat, rank in features_with_ranking_sorted]

# Print sorted feature rankings
print("Sorted Boruta feature rankings:")
for feat, rank in features_with_ranking_sorted:
    print(f"{feat}: {rank}")

# Plot importance
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.barh(sorted_features, sorted_rankings)
plt.xlabel('Boruta Ranking')
plt.title('Boruta Feature Importance (Sorted)')
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from boruta import BorutaPy
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE, ADASYN
from imblearn.combine import SMOTETomek
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix

# Assuming X_train_imputed, X_test_imputed, y_train, and y_test are already loaded DataFrames/arrays

# Define models
models = {
    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(),
    'NaiveBayes': GaussianNB(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

# Define feature selection and balancing techniques
feature_methods = ['PCA', 'Boruta']
balance_methods = ['SMOTE', 'ADASYN', 'ROSE']

# Function to apply PCA
def apply_pca(X_train, X_test, n_components=10):
    pca = PCA(n_components=n_components)
    X_train_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_train)
    X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test)
    return X_train_pca, X_test_pca

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=1)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Balancing functions
def balance_data(X_train, y_train, method):
    if method == 'SMOTE':
        smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    elif method == 'ADASYN':
        adasyn = ADASYN(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = adasyn.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    elif method == 'ROSE':
        rose = SMOTETomek(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = rose.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    return X_res, y_res

# Evaluation function
def evaluate_model(model, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    return f1, precision, recall, loss

# Collecting results
results = []
for feature_method in feature_methods:
    if feature_method == 'PCA':
        X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_pca(X_train_imputed, X_test_imputed)
    elif feature_method == 'Boruta':
        X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

    for balance_method in balance_methods:
        X_train_bal, y_train_bal = balance_data(X_train_fs, y_train, balance_method)
        
        # Apply scaling where necessary
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_bal_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)
        X_test_fs_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)

        for model_name, model in models.items():
            if model_name in ['SVM', 'KNN', 'LogisticRegression']:
                f1, precision, recall, loss = evaluate_model(model, X_train_bal_scaled, y_train_bal, X_test_fs_scaled, y_test)
            else:
                f1, precision, recall, loss = evaluate_model(model, X_train_bal, y_train_bal, X_test_fs, y_test)
            results.append([f'{feature_method}+{balance_method}', model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_df = pd.DataFrame(results, columns=['Method', 'Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])

# Plotting
fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))

# Plot F1 Score
x = np.arange(len(results_df['Method'].unique()))
width = 0.15

for i, model_name in enumerate(models.keys()):
    subset = results_df[results_df['Model'] == model_name]
    axs[0, 0].bar(x + i*width, subset['F1 Score'], width, label=model_name)
axs[0, 0].set_title('F1 Score')
axs[0, 0].set_xticks(x + width*(len(models)/2))
axs[0, 0].set_xticklabels(results_df['Method'].unique(), rotation=90)
axs[0, 0].legend()

# Plot Precision
for i, model_name in enumerate(models.keys()):
    subset = results_df[results_df['Model'] == model_name]
    axs[0, 1].bar(x + i*width, subset['Precision'], width, label=model_name)
axs[0, 1].set_title('Precision')
axs[0, 1].set_xticks(x + width*(len(models)/2))
axs[0, 1].set_xticklabels(results_df['Method'].unique(), rotation=90)
axs[0, 1].legend()

# Plot Recall
for i, model_name in enumerate(models.keys()):
    subset = results_df[results_df['Model'] == model_name]
    axs[1, 0].bar(x + i*width, subset['Recall'], width, label=model_name)
axs[1, 0].set_title('Recall')
axs[1, 0].set_xticks(x + width*(len(models)/2))
axs[1, 0].set_xticklabels(results_df['Method'].unique(), rotation=90)
axs[1, 0].legend()

# Plot Loss
for i, model_name in enumerate(models.keys()):
    subset = results_df[results_df['Model'] == model_name]
    axs[1, 1].bar(x + i*width, subset['Loss'], width, label=model_name)
axs[1, 1].set_title('Loss')
axs[1, 1].set_xticks(x + width*(len(models)/2))
axs[1, 1].set_xticklabels(results_df['Method'].unique(), rotation=90)
axs[1, 1].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from boruta import BorutaPy
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE, ADASYN
from imblearn.combine import SMOTETomek
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix

# Assuming X_train_imputed, X_test_imputed, y_train, and y_test are already loaded DataFrames/arrays

# Define models
models = {
    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(),
    'NaiveBayes': GaussianNB(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

# Define feature selection and balancing techniques
feature_methods = ['PCA', 'Boruta']
balance_methods = ['SMOTE', 'ADASYN', 'ROSE']

# Function to apply PCA
def apply_pca(X_train, X_test, n_components=10):
    pca = PCA(n_components=n_components)
    X_train_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_train)
    X_test_pca = pca.transform(X_test)
    return X_train_pca, X_test_pca

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=1)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Balancing functions
def balance_data(X_train, y_train, method):
    if method == 'SMOTE':
        smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    elif method == 'ADASYN':
        adasyn = ADASYN(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = adasyn.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    elif method == 'ROSE':
        rose = SMOTETomek(random_state=42)
        X_res, y_res = rose.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)
    return X_res, y_res

# Evaluation function
def evaluate_model(model, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test):
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    return f1, precision, recall, loss

# Collecting results
results = []
for feature_method in feature_methods:
    if feature_method == 'PCA':
        X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_pca(X_train_imputed, X_test_imputed)
    elif feature_method == 'Boruta':
        X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

    for balance_method in balance_methods:
        X_train_bal, y_train_bal = balance_data(X_train_fs, y_train, balance_method)
        
        # Apply scaling where necessary
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_bal_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)
        X_test_fs_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)

        for model_name, model in models.items():
            if model_name in ['SVM', 'KNN', 'LogisticRegression']:
                f1, precision, recall, loss = evaluate_model(model, X_train_bal_scaled, y_train_bal, X_test_fs_scaled, y_test)
            else:
                f1, precision, recall, loss = evaluate_model(model, X_train_bal, y_train_bal, X_test_fs, y_test)
            results.append([f'{feature_method}+{balance_method}', model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_df = pd.DataFrame(results, columns=['Method', 'Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])

# Pivot the DataFrame for heatmap
pivot_f1 = results_df.pivot(index="Method", columns="Model", values="F1 Score")
pivot_precision = results_df.pivot(index="Method", columns="Model", values="Precision")
pivot_loss = results_df.pivot(index="Method", columns="Model", values="Loss")

# Plotting the heatmap
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2,2, figsize=(25,8))
sns.heatmap(pivot_f1, annot=False, fmt=".2f", cmap="YlGnBu", ax=axes[0,0])
axes[0,0].set_title('F1 Score')
axes[0,0].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)
sns.heatmap(pivot_precision, annot=False, fmt=".2f", cmap="YlGnBu", ax=axes[0,1])
axes[0,1].set_title('Precision')
axes[0,1].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)
sns.heatmap(pivot_loss, annot=False, fmt=".2f", cmap="YlGnBu_r", ax=axes[1,1])
axes[1,1].set_title('Loss')
axes[1,1].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)

# Remove the last subplot
fig.delaxes(axes[1, 0])

# Adjust layout to increase spacing between rows
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.4)  # Adjust the value as needed



plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, KFold, cross_val_predict
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from boruta import BorutaPy
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# Define models and their parameter grids
models = {
    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(),
    'NaiveBayes': GaussianNB(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

param_grids = {
    'RandomForest': {
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'DecisionTree': {
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'LogisticRegression': {
        'C': [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100],
        'penalty': ['l1', 'l2'],
        'solver': ['liblinear']
    },
    'NaiveBayes': {},
    'SVM': {
        'C': [0.1, 1, 10],
        'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01],
        'kernel': ['rbf']
    },
    'KNN': {
        'n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7],
        'weights': ['uniform', 'distance']
    }
}

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=1)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Apply Boruta feature selection
# Assuming X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed are defined elsewhere
X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

# Apply SMOTE for balancing
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_fs, y_train)

# Initialize dictionaries to store results and confusion matrices
results_before = []
results_after = []
conf_matrices_before = {}
conf_matrices_after = {}

# Loop through each model
for model_name, model in models.items():
    if model_name == 'NaiveBayes':  # No hyperparameter tuning for Naive Bayes
        param_grid = {}
    else:
        param_grid = param_grids[model_name]

    # Apply scaling only to Logistic Regression, SVM, and KNN
    if model_name in ['LogisticRegression', 'SVM', 'KNN']:
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)  # Fit on training data
        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)  # Transform test data

    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

    # Before tuning
    y_pred_before = cross_val_predict(model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_before.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])
    conf_matrices_before[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)

    # Hyperparameter tuning and evaluation
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid, scoring='f1', cv=kf, n_jobs=-1)
    grid_search.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_

    # After tuning
    y_pred_after = cross_val_predict(best_model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_after.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_before_df = pd.DataFrame(results_before, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])
results_after_df = pd.DataFrame(results_after, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])

# Plotting before and after comparison
fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))

def plot_comparison(ax, metric, results_before_df, results_after_df):
    x = np.arange(len(results_before_df['Model']))
    width = 0.35

    ax.bar(x - width/2, results_before_df[metric], width, label='Before Tuning')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, results_after_df[metric], width, label='After Tuning')

    ax.set_title(metric)
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(results_before_df['Model'], rotation=45)
    ax.legend()

plot_comparison(axs[0, 0], 'F1 Score', results_before_df, results_after_df)
plot_comparison(axs[0, 1], 'Precision', results_before_df, results_after_df)
plot_comparison(axs[1, 0], 'Recall', results_before_df, results_after_df)
plot_comparison(axs[1, 1], 'Loss', results_before_df, results_after_df)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Plot FP, FN, TP, TN comparison for specific models before and after tuning
def plot_confusion_metrics(model_name, before_values, after_values):
    metrics = ['FP', 'FN', 'TP', 'TN']
    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.35

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(x - width/2, before_values, width, label='Before Tuning')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, after_values, width, label='After Tuning')

    ax.set_title(f'{model_name} Confusion Metrics Comparison Before and After Tuning')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)
    ax.legend()

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Example: Plot FP, FN, TP, TN for SVM
svm_before_values = [conf_matrices_before['SVM'][0, 1], conf_matrices_before['SVM'][1, 0],
                     conf_matrices_before['SVM'][1, 1], conf_matrices_before['SVM'][0, 0]]
svm_after_values = [conf_matrices_after['SVM'][0, 1], conf_matrices_after['SVM'][1, 0],
                    conf_matrices_after['SVM'][1, 1], conf_matrices_after['SVM'][0, 0]]

plot_confusion_metrics('SVM', svm_before_values, svm_after_values)

# Example: Plot FP, FN, TP, TN for Decision Tree
dt_before_values = [conf_matrices_before['DecisionTree'][0, 1], conf_matrices_before['DecisionTree'][1, 0],
                    conf_matrices_before['DecisionTree'][1, 1], conf_matrices_before['DecisionTree'][0, 0]]
dt_after_values = [conf_matrices_after['DecisionTree'][0, 1], conf_matrices_after['DecisionTree'][1, 0],
                   conf_matrices_after['DecisionTree'][1, 1], conf_matrices_after['DecisionTree'][0, 0]]

plot_confusion_metrics('Decision Tree', dt_before_values, dt_after_values)


rf_before_values = [conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][0, 1], conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][1, 0],

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, KFold, cross_val_predict
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from boruta import BorutaPy
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# Define models and their parameter grids
models = {
    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(),
    'NaiveBayes': GaussianNB(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

param_grids = {
    'RandomForest': {
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'DecisionTree': {
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'LogisticRegression': {
        'C': [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100],
        'penalty': ['l1', 'l2'],
        'solver': ['liblinear']
    },
    'NaiveBayes': {},
    'SVM': {
        'C': [0.1, 1, 10],
        'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01],
        'kernel': ['rbf']
    },
    'KNN': {
        'n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7],
        'weights': ['uniform', 'distance']
    }
}

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=1)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Apply Boruta feature selection
# Assuming X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed are defined elsewhere
X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

# Apply SMOTE for balancing
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_fs, y_train)

# Initialize dictionaries to store results and confusion matrices
results_before = []
results_after = []
conf_matrices_before = {}
conf_matrices_after = {}

# Loop through each model
for model_name, model in models.items():
    if model_name == 'NaiveBayes':  # No hyperparameter tuning for Naive Bayes
        param_grid = {}
    else:
        param_grid = param_grids[model_name]

    # Apply scaling only to Logistic Regression, SVM, and KNN
    if model_name in ['LogisticRegression', 'SVM', 'KNN']:
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)  # Fit on training data
        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)  # Transform test data

    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

    # Before tuning
    y_pred_before = cross_val_predict(model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_before.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])
    conf_matrices_before[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)

    # Hyperparameter tuning and evaluation
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid, scoring='f1', cv=kf, n_jobs=-1)
    grid_search.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_

    # After tuning
    y_pred_after = cross_val_predict(best_model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_after.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_before_df = pd.DataFrame(results_before, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])
results_after_df = pd.DataFrame(results_after, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])

    ax.set_title(metric)
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(results_before_df['Model'], rotation=45)
    ax.legend()

plot_comparison(axs[0, 0], 'F1 Score', results_before_df, results_after_df)

def plot_confusion_metrics(model_name, before_values, after_values):
    metrics = ['False Positive', 'False Negative', 'True Positive', 'True Negative']
    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.35

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(x - width/2, before_values, width, label='Before Tuning')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, after_values, width, label='After Tuning')

    ax.set_title(f'{model_name} Confusion Metrics Comparison Before and After Tuning')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)
    ax.legend()

    # Add labels with values above the bars
    for i, v in enumerate(before_values):
        ax.text(i - width/2, v + 0.01, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)
    for i, v in enumerate(after_values):
        ax.text(i + width/2, v + 0.01, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    if model_name == 'NaiveBayes':  # No hyperparameter tuning for Naive Bayes
        param_grid = {}
    else:
        param_grid = param_grids[model_name]

    # Lists to store metrics for each fold
    f1_scores = []

    recall_scores = []
    losses = []

    # Apply scaling only to Logistic Regression, SVM, and KNN

        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)  # Fit on training data

    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

    # Perform k-fold cross-validation
    for train_index, val_index in kf.split(X_train_scaled):
        X_train_fold, X_val_fold = X_train_scaled[train_index], X_train_scaled[val_index]
        y_train_fold, y_val_fold = y_train_bal[train_index], y_train_bal[val_index]

        # Before tuning

        y_pred_before = model.predict(X_val_fold)

    avg_f1 = np.mean(f1_scores)
    avg_precision = np.mean(precision_scores)
    avg_recall = np.mean(recall_scores)
    avg_loss = np.mean(losses)

    # Store results for before tuning

    grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid, scoring='f1', cv=kf, n_jobs=-1)
    grid_search.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)

    # Lists to store metrics after tuning
    f1_scores_after = []
    precision_scores_after = []
    recall_scores_after = []
    losses_after = []

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, cross_val_predict
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from boruta import BorutaPy
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# Define models and their parameter grids
models = {
    'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'LogisticRegression': LogisticRegression(),
    'NaiveBayes': GaussianNB(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier()
}

param_grids = {
    'RandomForest': {
        'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'DecisionTree': {
        'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
        'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
    },
    'LogisticRegression': {
        'C': [0.01, 0.1, 1, 10, 100],
        'penalty': ['l1', 'l2'],
        'solver': ['liblinear']
    },
    'NaiveBayes': {},
    'SVM': {
        'C': [0.1, 1, 10],
        'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01],
        'kernel': ['rbf']
    },
    'KNN': {
        'n_neighbors': [3, 5, 7],
        'weights': ['uniform', 'distance']
    }
}

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators=100, verbose=0, random_state=42)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Apply Boruta feature selection
# Assuming X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed are defined elsewhere
X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

# Apply SMOTE for balancing
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_fs, y_train)

# Initialize dictionaries to store results and confusion matrices
results_before = []
results_after = []
conf_matrices_before = {}
conf_matrices_after = {}

# Loop through each model
for model_name, model in models.items():
    if model_name == 'NaiveBayes':  # No hyperparameter tuning for Naive Bayes
        param_grid = {}
    else:
        param_grid = param_grids[model_name]

    # Apply scaling only to Logistic Regression, SVM, and KNN
    if model_name in ['LogisticRegression', 'SVM', 'KNN']:
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)  # Fit on training data
        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)  # Transform test data
    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    # Train model on entire training set
    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)

    # Evaluate on test set
    y_pred_test = model.predict(X_test_scaled)
    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000

    # Store results for before tuning
    results_before.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, loss])
    conf_matrices_before[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test)

    # Hyperparameter tuning and evaluation
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid, scoring='f1', cv=5, n_jobs=-1)
    grid_search.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_

    # Evaluate best model on test set
    y_pred_test_after = best_model.predict(X_test_scaled)
    f1_after = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    precision_after = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    recall_after = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    tn_after, fp_after, fn_after, tp_after = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test_after).ravel()
    loss_after = fp_after * 1000 + fn_after * 5000

    # Store results for after tuning
    results_after.append([model_name, f1_after, precision_after, recall_after, loss_after])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test_after)

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_before_df = pd.DataFrame(results_before, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])
results_after_df = pd.DataFrame(results_after, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Loss'])

# Plotting before and after comparison

def plot_comparison(ax, metric, results_before_df, results_after_df):
    x = np.arange(len(results_before_df['Model']))
    width = 0.35

    ax.bar(x - width/2, results_before_df[metric], width, label='Before Tuning', color='lightcoral')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, results_after_df[metric], width, label='After Tuning', color='skyblue')

    ax.set_xlabel('Model')
    ax.set_ylabel(metric)
    ax.set_title(f'{metric} Comparison Before and After Tuning')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(results_before_df['Model'], rotation=45)
    ax.legend()

plot_comparison(axs[0, 0], 'F1 Score', results_before_df, results_after_df)

# Plot FP, FN, TP, TN comparison for specific models before and after tuning
def plot_confusion_metrics(model_name, before_values, after_values):
    metrics = ['False Positive', 'False Negative', 'True Positive', 'True Negative']
    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.35

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(x - width/2, before_values, width, label='Before Tuning', color='lightcoral')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, after_values, width, label='After Tuning', color='skyblue')

    ax.set_xlabel('Metric')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title(f'{model_name} Confusion Metrics Comparison Before and After Tuning')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)
    ax.legend()

    # Add labels above bars
    for i, v in enumerate(before_values):
        ax.text(i - width/2, v + 100, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom')
    for i, v in enumerate(after_values):
        ax.text(i + width/2, v + 100, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Custom scoring function
def loss_cost(y_true, y_pred):
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    return -loss  # Negate the loss to make it a scoring function (higher is better)

# Make scorer
loss_scorer = make_scorer(loss_cost, greater_is_better=False)

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators=100, verbose=0, random_state=42)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)

    if model_name == 'NaiveBayes':  # No hyperparameter tuning for Naive Bayes
        param_grid = {}
    else:
        param_grid = param_grids[model_name]

        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)  # Transform test data
    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)

    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000

    conf_matrices_before[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test)

    best_params[model_name] = grid_search.best_params_

    # Evaluate best model on test set

    f1_after = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    precision_after = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    recall_after = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_test_after)
    tn_after, fp_after, fn_after, tp_after = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test_after).ravel()
    loss_after = fp_after * 1000 + fn_after * 5000

    # Store results for after tuning
    results_after.append([model_name, f1_after, precision_after, recall_after, loss_after])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test_after)

    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=42)

    if boruta.n_features_ == 0:

    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Custom scoring function for grid search
def custom_scorer(y_true, y_pred):
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)
    FP = cm[0, 1]
    FN = cm[1, 0]
    TP = cm[1, 1]
    # Custom score: maximize TP and minimize loss cost
    score = TP - (FP * 1000 + FN * 5000)
    return score

# Function to apply Boruta
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=42)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    if boruta.n_features_ == 0:
        raise ValueError("BorutaPy did not select any features.")
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Apply Boruta feature selection

    X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)
except ValueError as e:
    print(f"Error: {e}")
    # Handle the error (e.g., use original data without feature selection)
    X_train_fs, X_test_fs = X_train_imputed.values, X_test_imputed.values

# Apply SMOTE for balancing (if features are selected)
if X_train_fs.shape[1] > 0:
    smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
    X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_fs, y_train)

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, KFold, cross_val_predict
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from boruta import BorutaPy
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

# Define SVM and Random Forest classifiers
svm = SVC()
rf = RandomForestClassifier()

# Define parameter grids for SVM and Random Forest
param_grid_svm = {
    'C': [0.1, 1, 10],
    'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01],
    'kernel': ['rbf']
}

param_grid_rf = {
    'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200],
    'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30],
    'min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10]
}

# Function to apply Boruta for feature selection
def apply_boruta(X_train, y_train, X_test):
    rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
    boruta = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', verbose=0, random_state=1)
    boruta.fit(X_train.values, y_train)
    X_train_boruta = boruta.transform(X_train.values)
    X_test_boruta = boruta.transform(X_test.values)
    return X_train_boruta, X_test_boruta

# Apply Boruta feature selection
# Assuming X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed are defined elsewhere
X_train_fs, X_test_fs = apply_boruta(X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed)

# Apply SMOTE for balancing
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_bal, y_train_bal = smote.fit_resample(X_train_fs, y_train)

# Initialize lists to store results and confusion matrices
results_before = []
results_after = []
conf_matrices_before = {}
conf_matrices_after = {}

# Loop through SVM and Random Forest models
for model_name, model, param_grid in [('SVM', svm, param_grid_svm), ('RandomForest', rf, param_grid_rf)]:
    # Apply scaling only to SVM
    if model_name == 'SVM':
        scaler = StandardScaler()
        X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_bal)  # Fit on training data
        X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_fs)  # Transform test data
    else:
        X_train_scaled = X_train_bal
        X_test_scaled = X_test_fs

    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

    # Before tuning
    y_pred_before = cross_val_predict(model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_before.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, accuracy, loss])
    conf_matrices_before[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_before)

    # Hyperparameter tuning and evaluation
    grid_search = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid, scoring='f1', cv=kf, n_jobs=-1)
    grid_search.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train_bal)
    best_model = grid_search.best_estimator_

    # After tuning
    y_pred_after = cross_val_predict(best_model, X_train_scaled, y_train_bal, cv=kf)
    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_after.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, accuracy, loss])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)

# Convert results to DataFrames
results_before_df = pd.DataFrame(results_before, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Accuracy', 'Loss'])
results_after_df = pd.DataFrame(results_after, columns=['Model', 'F1 Score', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'Accuracy', 'Loss'])

# Function to plot comparison
def plot_comparison(ax, metric, results_before_df, results_after_df, models_to_plot):
    x = np.arange(len(models_to_plot))
    width = 0.35

    if metric == 'Loss':
        before_values = results_before_df.loc[results_before_df['Model'].isin(models_to_plot), metric].values / 1000
        after_values = results_after_df.loc[results_after_df['Model'].isin(models_to_plot), metric].values / 1000
    else:
        before_values = results_before_df.loc[results_before_df['Model'].isin(models_to_plot), metric].values
        after_values = results_after_df.loc[results_after_df['Model'].isin(models_to_plot), metric].values

    ax.bar(x - width/2, before_values, width, label='Before Tuning')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, after_values, width, label='After Tuning')

    ax.set_title(metric)
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(models_to_plot, rotation=45)
    ax.legend()

    # Add labels with values above the bars
    for i, v in enumerate(before_values):
        if metric == 'Loss':
            ax.text(i - width/2, v + 0.1, f'{v:.2f}K', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)
        else:
            ax.text(i - width/2, v + 0.01, f'{v:.3f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)
    for i, v in enumerate(after_values):
        if metric == 'Loss':
            ax.text(i + width/2, v + 0.1, f'{v:.2f}K', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)
        else:
            ax.text(i + width/2, v + 0.01, f'{v:.3f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)

# Plotting before and after comparison for SVM and RandomForest
fig, axs = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(15, 15))

plot_comparison(axs[0, 0], 'F1 Score', results_before_df, results_after_df, ['SVM', 'RandomForest'])
plot_comparison(axs[0, 1], 'Precision', results_before_df, results_after_df, ['SVM', 'RandomForest'])
plot_comparison(axs[1, 0], 'Recall', results_before_df, results_after_df, ['SVM', 'RandomForest'])
plot_comparison(axs[1, 1], 'Accuracy', results_before_df, results_after_df, ['SVM', 'RandomForest'])
plot_comparison(axs[2, 0], 'Loss', results_before_df, results_after_df, ['SVM', 'RandomForest'])

# Plotting confusion matrix metrics for SVM and RandomForest
def plot_confusion_metrics(ax, model_name, before_values, after_values):
    metrics = ['True Positive', 'True Negative', 'False Positive', 'False Negative']
    x = np.arange(len(metrics))
    width = 0.35

    ax.bar(x - width/2, before_values, width, label='Before Tuning')
    ax.bar(x + width/2, after_values, width, label='After Tuning')

    ax.set_title(f'{model_name} Confusion Metrics')
    ax.set_xticks(x)
    ax.set_xticklabels(metrics)
    ax.legend()

    # Add labels with values above the bars
    for i, v in enumerate(before_values):
        ax.text(i - width/2, v + 0.01, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)
    for i, v in enumerate(after_values):
        ax.text(i + width/2, v + 0.01, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)

# Calculate confusion matrix metrics for SVM
svm_before_values = [conf_matrices_before['SVM'][1, 1], conf_matrices_before['SVM'][0, 0],
                     conf_matrices_before['SVM'][0, 1], conf_matrices_before['SVM'][1, 0]]
svm_after_values = [conf_matrices_after['SVM'][1, 1], conf_matrices_after['SVM'][0, 0],
                    conf_matrices_after['SVM'][0, 1], conf_matrices_after['SVM'][1, 0]]

# Calculate confusion matrix metrics for RandomForest
rf_before_values = [conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][1, 1], conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][0, 0],
                    conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][0, 1], conf_matrices_before['RandomForest'][1, 0]]
rf_after_values = [conf_matrices_after['RandomForest'][1, 1], conf_matrices_after['RandomForest'][0, 0],
                   conf_matrices_after['RandomForest'][0, 1], conf_matrices_after['RandomForest'][1, 0]]

plot_confusion_metrics(axs[2, 1], 'SVM', svm_before_values, svm_after_values)

    f1 = f1_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    precision = precision_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    recall = recall_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after).ravel()
    loss = fp * 1000 + fn * 5000
    results_after.append([model_name, f1, precision, recall, accuracy, loss])
    conf_matrices_after[model_name] = confusion_matrix(y_train_bal, y_pred_after)

# Convert results to DataFrames

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.impute import KNNImputer
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.metrics import precision_score, recall_score, roc_auc_score, f1_score, confusion_matrix, roc_curve, auc
from boruta import BorutaPy
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming X_train_imputed, y_train, X_test_imputed, y_test are already defined
X_train = X_train_imputed.copy()
y_train = y_train.copy()
X_test = X_test_imputed.copy()
y_test = y_test.copy()

# Boruta Feature Selection
rf = RandomForestClassifier(n_jobs=-1, class_weight='balanced', max_depth=5)
feat_selector = BorutaPy(rf, n_estimators='auto', random_state=1)
feat_selector.fit(X_train.values, y_train.values)

X_train_selected = feat_selector.transform(X_train.values)
X_test_selected = feat_selector.transform(X_test.values)

# SMOTE Data Balancing
sm = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_res, y_train_res = sm.fit_resample(X_train_selected, y_train)

# Scaling the Features
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
X_train_res = scaler.fit_transform(X_train_res)
X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test_selected)

# Build and Train SVM Model
svm = SVC(probability=True)
svm.fit(X_train_res, y_train_res)

# Predictions and Evaluation
y_pred = svm.predict(X_test_scaled)
y_pred_prob = svm.predict_proba(X_test_scaled)[:, 1]

precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred)
recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred)
f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)
roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_prob)
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)

# Calculate loss cost
cost_fp = 1000
cost_fn = 5000
FP = conf_matrix[0, 1]
FN = conf_matrix[1, 0]
loss_cost = cost_fp * FP + cost_fn * FN

# Print the results
print("Precision:", precision)
print("Recall:", recall)
print("F1 Score:", f1)
print("ROC AUC:", roc_auc)
print("Confusion Matrix:\n", conf_matrix)
print("Loss Cost:", loss_cost)

# ROC Curve
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

# Plot ROC Curve
plt.figure()
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color='darkorange', lw=2, label='ROC curve (area = %0.2f)' % roc_auc)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='navy', lw=2, linestyle='--')
plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show()
